      "prompt": "\n\nThe following skills provide specialized instructions for specific tasks.\nUse the read tool to load a skill's file when the task matches its description.\nWhen a skill file references a relative path, resolve it against the skill directory (parent of SKILL.md / dirname of the path) and use that absolute path in tool commands.\n\n<available_skills>\n  <skill>\n    <name>healthcheck</name>\n    <description>Host security hardening and risk-tolerance configuration for OpenClaw deployments. Use when a user asks for security audits, firewall/SSH/update hardening, risk posture, exposure review, OpenClaw cron scheduling for periodic checks, or version status checks on a machine running OpenClaw (laptop, workstation, Pi, VPS).</description>\n    <location>~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md</location>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>openai-image-gen</name>\n    <description>Batch-generate images via OpenAI Images API. Random prompt sampler + `index.html` gallery.</description>\n    <location>~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/openai-image-gen/SKILL.md</location>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>openai-whisper-api</name>\n    <description>Transcribe audio via OpenAI Audio Transcriptions API (Whisper).</description>\n    <location>~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/openai-whisper-api/SKILL.md</location>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>skill-creator</name>\n    <description>Create or update AgentSkills. Use when designing, structuring, or packaging skills with scripts, references, and assets.</description>\n    <location>~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md</location>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>weather</name>\n    <description>Get current weather and forecasts via wttr.in or Open-Meteo. Use when: user asks about weather, temperature, or forecasts for any location. NOT for: historical weather data, severe weather alerts, or detailed meteorological analysis. No API key needed.</description>\n    <location>~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/weather/SKILL.md</location>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>agent-watchdog</name>\n    <description>Monitors running agents and detects stalls caused by model hangs or execution deadlocks. Attempts automatic recovery and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop.</description>\n    <location>~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md</location>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>error-learning-loop</name>\n    <description>Capture errors and near-misses from the current task and from sub-agent handoff reports, perform semantic deduplication of incidents, convert them into actionable learnings, and promote guardrails into AGENTS.md and TOOLS.md so the main agent avoids repeating mistakes. Supports manual invocation and end-of-task wrap-up.</description>\n    <location>~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/SKILL.md</location>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>long-prompt-orchestrator</name>\n    <description>A production-ready Long Prompt Optimizer that automatically decomposes overly long/complex tasks into smaller dependent mini-prompts executed sequentially, manages token budgets, maintains persistent ToDo checklists, validates final output, supports recovery from interruptions, and includes context lifecycle management, semantic indexing, session management, and dynamic agent memory routing.</description>\n    <location>~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/SKILL.md</location>\n  </skill>\n  <skill>\n    <name>salesforce-architect</name>\n    <description>Production-ready skill for analyzing complex business processes, extracting requirements, producing Salesforce architecture decisions, generating FIT/GAP analysis, functional design documentation, data models, and validating architecture using official Salesforce documentation only.</description>\n    <location>~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/SKILL.